    "b-00-system-overview-what-this-repository-is-1": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-what-this-repository-is-1",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "docs-system: system architecture"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-docs-system-is-codecai-2": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-docs-system-is-codecai-2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "docs-system",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " is Codecaine's documentation infrastructure: a layered implementation\npipeline built around a block-based document format ("
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "), the tooling that reads/writes/serves it, and a\nbrowser workbench for humans "
        },
        {
          "insert": "and",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " agents to read, edit, and annotate docs."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-the-one-sentence-philoso-3": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-the-one-sentence-philoso-3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The foundation layer carries the philosophy; this overview focuses on the\nimplementation shape: "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs are structured data, not markdown\nfiles.",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " Every document is a normalized tree of typed blocks with stable\nids, which lets the pipeline address a precise block instead of a whole file.\nAn agent can say\n\"change "
        },
        {
          "insert": "this",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " block\", a comment can anchor to "
        },
        {
          "insert": "this",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " paragraph and survive\nedits around it, a backlink can point at "
        },
        {
          "insert": "this",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " exact card, and a save can\nbe expressed as a minimal batch of block operations instead of a whole-file\nrewrite."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-every-block-is-one-of-15": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-every-block-is-one-of-15",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Every block is one of "
        },
        {
          "insert": "14 types",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ": paragraph, heading, list-item, quote, code,\ncallout, divider, structured-table, file-tree, interaction-surface, mermaid,\ncanvas, image, and video. Retired MDX-era types (the old semantic cards,\n"
        },
        {
          "insert": "data-model",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", "
        },
        {
          "insert": "api-surface",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", …) coerce to "
        },
        {
          "insert": "callout",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " on read, with the old type\nname preserved as "
        },
        {
          "insert": "props.kind",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ". The full vocabulary — every type's props and\nits typed actions — is documented in "
        },
        {
          "insert": "Block vocabulary & typed actions",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "10-system-design/40-block-vocabulary"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-the-pipeline-at-a-glance-4": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-the-pipeline-at-a-glance-4",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "The pipeline at a glance"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-code-5": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-code-5",
      "type": "code",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "                    ┌─────────────┐\n   authoring        │  docs-model │   pure schema + ops (no I/O, no React)\n   (markdown ───►   └──────┬──────┘\n    migrate,               │\n    or live edit)   ┌──────┴──────┐\n                    │ docs-index  │   sqlite backlinks index (derived, rebuildable)\n                    └──────┬──────┘\n                    ┌──────┴──────┐\n                    │ docs-server │   mutation authority: locks, hashes, undo, SSE\n                    └──────┬──────┘\n                    ┌──────┴──────┐\n                    │ docs-viewer │   React rendering + TipTap editor + targeting\n                    └──────┬──────┘\n                    ┌──────┴──────┐\n                    │docs-workbench│  the runnable app (serve + static export)\n                    └──────┬──────┘\n                    ┌──────┴──────┐\n                    │  docs-cli   │   `docs` command: serve, export, migrate, …\n                    └─────────────┘"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-each-layer-only-depends-6": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-each-layer-only-depends-6",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Each layer only depends on the layers above it in this list. The\n"
        },
        {
          "insert": "package map",
          "attributes": {
            "reference": {
              "kind": "doc",
              "path": "20-implementation/10-packages"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " walks through every package in\ndetail."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-where-content-lives-7": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-where-content-lives-7",
      "type": "heading",
      "props": {
        "level": 2
      },
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Where content lives"
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-a-document-is-a-bundle-8": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-a-document-is-a-bundle-8",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "A document is a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "bundle",
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ": a folder holding "
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (the block tree),\noptional "
        },
        {
          "insert": "comments.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (annotations), and an "
        },
        {
          "insert": "assets/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " folder for images\nand canvas sidecars. Bundles live in a "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "docs"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " tree owned by whichever\nproject the docs are "
        },
        {
          "insert": "about",
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " — the canvas repo has "
        },
        {
          "insert": "canvas/docs/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", and this\nrepo has its own "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs/",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true,
            "reference": {
              "kind": "source",
              "path": "docs"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " (the one you are reading right now)."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
    "b-00-system-overview-markdown-is-an-on-ramp-9": {
      "id": "b-00-system-overview-markdown-is-an-on-ramp-9",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "props": {},
      "text": [
        {
          "insert": "Markdown is an on-ramp, not the storage format: "
        },
        {
          "insert": "docs migrate",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " converts an\nexisting "
        },
        {
          "insert": ".md",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "/"
        },
        {
          "insert": ".mdx",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " tree into bundles once, and from then on the workbench\n(or an agent driving the ops API) edits "
        },
        {
          "insert": "doc.json",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": " directly. Edits are\nexpressed in a seven-op kernel — six generic structural/text ops plus\n"
        },
        {
          "insert": "blockAction",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": ", which invokes one of 13 typed actions on structured blocks\n(tables, file trees, interaction surfaces, code annotations) — and an agent\ncan discover the whole edit surface from "
        },
        {
          "insert": "GET /api/blocks",
          "attributes": {
            "code": true
          }
        },
        {
          "insert": "."
        }
      ],
      "children": []
    },
